        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## Ranking Cd²⁺, Pb²⁺, and Hg²⁺ by log K₁ with Thiocyanic Acid (SCN⁻)\n\nUsing the 1:1 complex formation equilibrium **[M] + [L] ⇌ [ML]** (beta_def_812) at **25 °C** in aqueous solution, the NIST SRD-46 database gives:\n\n| Metal | log K₁ | T (°C) | I (M) | VLM ID |\n|-------|--------|--------|-------|--------|\n| **Hg²⁺** | **9.64** | 25 | 0 | vlm_172457 |\n| **Cd²⁺** | **1.93** | 25 | 0 | vlm_172411 |\n| **Pb²⁺** | **0.49 – 1.08** | 25 | 1–4 | vlm_172483–172486 |\n\n> Note: No log K value at I = 0 was available for Pb²⁺ in SRD-46; the closest entries range from 0.49 (I = 1 M) to 1.08 (I = 4 M). At comparable ionic strength (I = 1 M), Cd²⁺ gives log K₁ = 1.31 vs. Pb²⁺ = 0.49, confirming the ranking.",
